obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (14362)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 18
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14362&sectionno=12&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `[Power to confer rights of Indian citizen or citizens of certain country.] Omitted by s. 10, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-12-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (14363)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 19
  title `Certificate of Citizenship in case of doubt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14363&sectionno=13&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, in such cases as`
  line `it thinks fit, certify that a person with respect to whose citizenship of India a doubt exists, is a citizen`
  line `of India; and a certificate issued under this section shall, unless it is proved that it was obtained by`
  line `means of fraud, false representation or concealment of any material fact, be conclusive evidence that`
  line `person was such a citizen on the date thereof, but without prejudice to any evidence that he was such a`
  line `citizen at an earlier date.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (14364)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 20
  title `Disposal of application under sections 5, 6 and 7A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 2004, s. 11, for "sections 5 and 6" (w.e.f. 3-12-2004)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14364&sectionno=14&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The prescribed authority or the`
  line `Central Government may, in its discretion, grant or refuse an application under ^1`
  line `[sections 5, 6 and`
  line `7A] and shall not be required to assign any reasons for such grant or refusal.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section l5 the decision of the prescribed authority or the Central`
  line `Government on any such application as aforesaid shall be final and shall not be called in question in`
  line `any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (14365)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 21
  title `Issue of national identity cards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-12-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14365&sectionno=14A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Issue of national identity cards.―(1) The Central Government may compulsorily`
  line `register every citizen of India and issue national identity card to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may maintain a National Register of Indian Citizens and for that`
  line `purpose establish a National Registration Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the date of commencement of the Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 2003 (6 of`
  line `2004), the Registrar General, India, appointed under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Registration of`
  line `Births and Deaths Act, 1969 (18 of 1969) shall act as the National Registration Authority and he shall`
  line `function as the Registrar General of Citizen Registration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may appoint such other officers and staff as may be required to assist`
  line `the Registrar General of Citizen Registration in discharging his functions and responsibilities.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure to be followed in compulsory registration of the citizens of India shall be such`
  line `as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (14366)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 22
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14366&sectionno=15&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made under this Act by the prescribed`
  line `authority or any officer or other authority (other than the Central Government) may, within a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date of the order, make an application to the Central Government for a revision of`
  line `that order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may entertain the application after the expiry of the said`
  line `period of thirty days, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause from making`
  line `the application in time.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of any such application under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall, after`
  line `considering the application of the aggrieved person and any report thereon which the officer or`
  line `authority making the order may submit, make such order in relation to the application as it deems fit,`
  line `and the decision of the Central Government shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (14367)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 23
  title Review.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-12-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14367&sectionno=15A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[15A. Review.―(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the Central Government, may,`
  line `within thirty days from the date of such order, make an application for review of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may entertain an application after the expiry of the said`
  line `period of thirty days, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause from making`
  line `the application in time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an application for a review of an order passed in terms of the provisions of`
  line `section 14A shall be disposed of in the manner provided for in the procedure as may be laid down`
  line `under clause (ia) of sub-section (2) of section 18.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall, make such`
  line `order as it deems fit, and the decision of the Central Government on such review shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (14368)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 24
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14368&sectionno=16&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order, direct that any power which`
  line `is conferred on it by any of the provisions of this Act other than those of section 10 and section 18`
  line `shall, in such circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, be`
  line `exercisable also by such officer or authority as may be so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (14369)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 25
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14369&sectionno=17&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, for the purpose of procuring anything to be done or not to be`
  line `done under this Act, knowingly makes any representation which is false in a material particular shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^1`
  line `[five years], or ^2`
  line `[with fine which`
  line `may extend to fifty thousand rupees], or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 2004, s. 14, for "six months" (w.e.f. 3-12-2004)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "with fine" (w.e.f. 3-12-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (14370)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455&sectionId=14370&sectionno=18&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00001_195557_1517807319455
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for`
  line
  line `(a) the registration of anything required or authorised under this Act to be registered, and the`
  line `conditions and restrictions in regard to such registration;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the form and manner in which a declaration under sub-section (1) of section 4 shall be`
  line made;;
  line
  line `(b) the forms to be used and the registers to be maintained under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the administration and taking of oaths of allegiance under this Act and the time within`
  line `which and the manner in which, such oaths shall be taken and recorded;`
  line
  line `(d) the giving of any notice required or authorised to be given by any person under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the cancellation of the registration of, and the cancellation and amendment of certificates`
  line `of naturalisation relating to, persons deprived of citizenship under this Act, and the delivering up`
  line `of such certificates for those purposes;`
  line
  line `^2[(ee) the manner and form in which and the authority to whom declarations referred to in`
  line `clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (6) of section 6A shall be submitted and other matters connected`
  line `with such declarations;]`
  line
  line `^3[(eei) the conditions, restrictions and manner for granting certificate of registration or certificate`
  line `of naturalisation under sub-section (1) of section 6B;]`
  line
  line `^4[(eea) the conditions and the manner subject to which a person may be registered as an`
  line `Overseas Citizen of India Cardholder under sub-section (1) of section 7A;`
  line
  line `(eeb) the manner of making declaration for renunciation of Overseas Citizen of India Card`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 7C;]`
  line
  line `(f) the registration at Indian consulates of the births and deaths of persons of any class or`
  line `description born or dying outside India;`
  line
  line `(g) the levy and collection of fees in respect of applications, registrations, declarations and`
  line `certificates under this Act, in respect of the taking of an oath of allegiance, and in respect of the`
  line `supply of certified or other copies of documents;`
  line
  line `(h) the authority to determine the question of acquisition of citizenship of another country, the`
  line `procedure to be followed by such authority and rules of evidence relating to such cases;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure to be followed by the committees of inquiry appointed under section 10 and`
  line `the conferment on such committees of any of the powers, rights and privileges of civil courts;`
  line
  line `^5[(ia) the procedure to be followed in compulsory registration of the citizens of India under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 14A;]`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which applications for revision may be made and the procedure to be`
  line `followed by the Central Government in dealing with such applications; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed under the Act.`
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule under this section, the Central Government may provide that a breach`
  line `thereof shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[Provided that any rule made in respect of a matter specified in clause (ia) of sub-section (2) may`
  line `provide that a breach thereof shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both].`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(4) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of session,`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule].`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-12-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 65 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 7-12-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 47 of 2019, s. 5 (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 1 of 2015, s. 5 (w.e.f. 6-1-2015).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso ins. by Act 6 of 2004, s. 15 (w.e.f. 3-12-2004).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 15-5-1986)`
